cs.DB, cs.DC, cs.OS, cs.Distributed, cs.PL 

This paper discusses a new approach to database management system architecture, specifically focusing on transactional and data components. Therefore, it is most likely to belong to the cs.DB (Databases) sub-category. Additionally, it discusses the potential for exploiting multi-core hardware, which could fall under the cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) sub-category. The paper also mentions the potential for enabling flexible transactions in cloud database deployments, which could fall under the cs.OS (Operating Systems) and cs.Distributed (Distributed Computing) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses implementation issues, which could fall under the cs.PL (Programming Languages) sub-category.
